   "body" : "There's no harm in calling `disconnect_nodes` for nodes that weren't connected (in this case it's a no-op).  However, detecting this case and logging a warning can help ensure that tests are behaving as expected.\r\n\r\nIn addition, since `disconnect_nodes` works bidirectionally, I removed all instances of this pattern:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndisconnect_nodes(self.nodes[0], 1)\r\ndisconnect_nodes(self.nodes[1], 0)\r\n```",
